
All are categorized as Big Data processing and distribution.

# Dataproc
1. Dataproc supports manual provision to cluster and If one prefers a hands-on Dev-ops approach, then choose Datapro
2. Also, If systems are Hadoop dependent, then it is wise to choose Dataproc over Dataflow or Dataprep.

# Data Flow: 
Dataflow supports automatic provision to clusters. 
if you prefer a serverless approach, then select Dataflow


# Dataprep
helps to prepare and clean the data for future use.
Dataprep, on the other hand, is UI-driven.
